NOTE ON NAMING:
  "Admin" and "Editor" are used interchangeably here.
  The role that can see real names = ADMIN/EDITOR (role = 1)
  The role that owns study records = STUDENT (role = 2)
  Guests are unregistered viewers (role = 0)

STRUCT HIERARCHY:
│
├── UserAccount
│     ├── userID          (int)
│     ├── username        (char[])   ← PUBLIC, shown on leaderboard
│     ├── fullName        (char[])   ← PRIVATE, admin-only visible
│     ├── password        (char[])   ← XOR encrypted
│     └── role            (int)      ← 0=guest, 1=admin, 2=student
│
└── StudyRecord
      ├── recordID        (int)
      ├── ownerUsername   (char[])   ← links record to student
      ├── subject         (char[])
      ├── hoursStudied    (float)
      ├── xpEarned        (int)      ← calculated from hours
      └── date            (char[])

/* ─── User Account Struct ─── */
typedef struct {
    int     userID;
    char    username[MAX_USERNAME];     /* public display name    */
    char    fullName[MAX_FULLNAME];     /* private, admin-only    */
    char    password[MAX_PASSWORD];     /* XOR encrypted          */
    int     role;                       /* 0=guest 1=admin 2=stud */
} UserAccount;

/* ─── Study Record Struct ─── */
typedef struct {
    int     recordID;
    char    ownerUsername[MAX_USERNAME];
    char    subject[MAX_SUBJECT];
    float   hoursStudied;
    int     xpEarned;
    char    date[MAX_DATE];
} StudyRecord;

/* ─── Leaderboard Entry Struct ─── */
/* Built at runtime, NOT stored in file */
typedef struct {
    char    username[MAX_USERNAME];     /* always shown           */
    char    fullName[MAX_FULLNAME];     /* shown only to admin    */
    int     totalXP;
    int     rank;                       /* 1, 2, or 3             */
} LeaderboardEntry;

LEADERBOARD CONSTRUCTION (runtime, not stored):

STEP 1: Aggregate XP per student username
        → loop through StudyRecord[]
        → sum xpEarned grouped by ownerUsername

STEP 2: Match username to UserAccount[]
        → retrieve fullName (for admin display)
        → confirm role == STUDENT (role = 2)
        → guests and admins are excluded

STEP 3: Sort aggregated results by totalXP (descending)
        → selection sort on LeaderboardEntry[]

STEP 4: Take top 3 entries
        → assign rank 1, 2, 3

STEP 5: Display based on viewer's role
        → GUEST / STUDENT → show username only
        → ADMIN / EDITOR  → show username + full name

