TIE-BREAKING:
  If two students have equal totalXP:
    → The student with MORE total hours studied ranks higher
    → If still tied → earlier registration (lower userID) ranks higher

  This ensures deterministic ranking at all times.

EDGE CASES TO HANDLE:
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ 1. Fewer than 3 students exist                               │
│    → Show only available ranks (e.g., only Top 1 or Top 2)  │
│                                                              │
│ 2. Student has no study records yet                          │
│    → totalXP = 0, still eligible but ranks last             │
│    → Only show students with at least 1 record              │
│                                                              │
│ 3. Admin/Guest accounts in UserAccount[]                     │
│    → Filter by role == STUDENT before building leaderboard  │
│                                                              │
│ 4. Deleted records affect leaderboard                        │
│    → Leaderboard is always rebuilt from current records[]   │
│    → No stale cached data                                    │
