ENCRYPTED FIELDS:
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  password  → XOR encrypted before writing to file           │
│  fullName  → XOR encrypted before writing to file           │
│             (extra privacy layer for student real names)    │
│                                                              │
│  username  → stored in plaintext (public identifier)        │
│  role      → stored as integer (not sensitive)              │
│  subject   → stored in plaintext (not sensitive)            │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

FOR PASSWORD ENCRYPTION:
  key = username + MASTER_KEY_CHAR

FOR FULL NAME ENCRYPTION:
  key = username + password + MASTER_KEY_CHAR
  (stronger key since fullName is more sensitive)

ENCRYPTION FORMULA:
  encrypted[i] = plaintext[i] XOR key[i % keyLen]

DECRYPTION:
  Same function — XOR is self-inverse
  Only admin can trigger fullName decryption display

FILES:
├── users.txt      ← UserAccount records
└── records.txt    ← StudyRecord records

users.txt FORMAT (per line):
userID|username|encryptedFullName|encryptedPassword|role

EXAMPLE:
1|SpawnMaster99|%#@$^&*!|#$%^&*()|2
2|AdminUser|||||1
(fullName field empty or placeholder for non-students)

records.txt FORMAT (per line):
recordID|ownerUsername|subject|hoursStudied|xpEarned|date

EXAMPLE:
1|SpawnMaster99|Mathematics|2.5|275|2025-06-15
2|SpawnMaster99|Physics|1.0|100|2025-06-16
3|StudyKing07|Chemistry|3.0|350|2025-06-15

LOADING:
  fopen(READ) → parse line by line with fgets
  → tokenize with strtok (delimiter = '|')
  → populate struct arrays
  → decrypt fullName and password in memory only
  → fclose

SAVING:
  fopen(WRITE) → overwrite entire file
  → encrypt fullName and password before writing
  → fprintf each struct
  → fclose

SECURITY NOTE:
  Decrypted fullName and password exist ONLY in RAM
  during program execution. File always stores encrypted.

